\begin_inset Formula $f(X):=\frac{X^{p}-1}{X-1}=X^{p-1}+X^{p-2}+\dots+X+1$
\end_inset

 es irreducible en 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Q}[X]$
\end_inset

