\begin_inset Formula $(X-1)f(X)=X^{p}-1$
\end_inset

, queda 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Xf(X+1)=(X+1)^{p}-1=X^{p}+\binom{p}{1}X^{p-1}+\dots+\binom{p}{p-1}X,
\]

\end_inset

luego 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f(X+1)=X^{p-1}+\binom{p}{1}X^{p-2}+\dots+\binom{p}{p-1},
\]

\end_inset

que es irreducible por Eisenstein porque 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

